-- UBS to appeal French court's demand for 1.1 bln euros 
-- By Alice Baghdjian
-- Mon Sep 22, 2014 10:51AM EDT
-- None



ZURICH, Sept 22 (Reuters) - Swiss bank UBS <UBSN.VX> said on Monday that it will appeal against a French court ruling that it must deposit a 1.1 billion euro ($1.41 billion) guarantee for potential fines it may have to pay if found guilty of helping rich French clients avoid tax.

